1
00:00:00,320 --> 00:00:05,360
This series is a work of fiction inspired
by questions that arise within the human heart.

2
00:00:05,380 --> 00:00:09,760
It is not intended to offend or pass judgment
on any beliefs, religions, or individuals.

3
00:00:10,091 --> 00:00:11,979
(Previuos Chapter)
Hey! Joe's here!

4
00:00:13,848 --> 00:00:15,410
Listen carefully to your heart.

5
00:00:17,090 --> 00:00:18,099
What about you, Tanrak?

6
00:00:19,820 --> 00:00:20,920
Have you ever had doubts?

7
00:00:21,231 --> 00:00:25,299
There are still things
that make me…waver.

8
00:00:25,571 --> 00:00:26,899
If one day I have to choose,

9
00:00:27,602 --> 00:00:30,280
I'd choose God over anything else.

10
00:00:30,490 --> 00:00:32,801
My dad died. My mom went to prison.

11
00:00:33,121 --> 00:00:34,521
So I ended up as a scholarship kid.

12
00:00:34,842 --> 00:00:37,410
Are you still going to ask me
why I don't believe in God?

13
00:00:37,817 --> 00:00:40,900
I'll pray to God for your mom.

14
00:00:50,040 --> 00:00:58,970
REPENT, THEN, AND TURN TO GOD,
SO THAT YOUR SINS MAY BE WIPED OUT
ACTS 3:19

15
00:01:09,090 --> 00:01:11,530
My mom taught me to do it like this.
We each do half the work.

16
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:14,500
Alright.

17
00:01:17,823 --> 00:01:18,823
Kind of a shame, huh?

18
00:01:19,725 --> 00:01:21,096
School's about to start.

19
00:01:21,630 --> 00:01:23,700
Soon everyone's gonna be back.

20
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:28,990
I thought you said
you weren't making up with him.

21
00:01:29,948 --> 00:01:31,108
But you're wearing his shirt.

22
00:01:34,297 --> 00:01:35,973
I don't like being mad at people.

23
00:01:36,336 --> 00:01:37,404
It makes me uncomfortable.

24
00:01:40,146 --> 00:01:41,201
I see.

25
00:01:42,702 --> 00:01:44,000
Now you two are good.

26
00:01:44,733 --> 00:01:46,198
So my time's up, huh?

27
00:02:00,560 --> 00:02:01,900
That's time for a friend.

28
00:02:08,370 --> 00:02:09,499
Then who am I?

29
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:25,500
"Ticket to Heaven"
(Episode 5)

30
00:03:27,230 --> 00:03:27,869
See?

31
00:03:27,888 --> 00:03:29,640
I told you you're about the same size.

32
00:03:29,663 --> 00:03:30,989
It fits perfectly.

33
00:03:31,235 --> 00:03:32,235
Yeah.

34
00:03:33,060 --> 00:03:34,060
You look good.

35
00:03:35,263 --> 00:03:37,431
So, what's the decision?

36
00:03:37,580 --> 00:03:39,296
You've made up your mind, right? Hm?

37
00:03:40,274 --> 00:03:41,183
About what, Mommy?

38
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,300
You know, that thing.

39
00:03:43,825 --> 00:03:44,774
Ask him.

40
00:03:44,794 --> 00:03:46,300
Don't ask me. I don't know.

41
00:03:52,287 --> 00:03:53,527
What are you smiling at, Barth?

42
00:03:56,379 --> 00:03:57,680
What did you want to ask me?

43
00:03:57,795 --> 00:04:00,601
You're going on to the seminary
with Kongdech, right?

44
00:04:00,761 --> 00:04:01,761
Right?

45
00:04:02,800 --> 00:04:04,265
Oh, well…

46
00:04:04,405 --> 00:04:07,244
Come on, you've known each other
since you were kids.

47
00:04:07,270 --> 00:04:08,997
It'd be nice if you went together.

48
00:04:09,770 --> 00:04:12,595
Take a good look at each other now.

49
00:04:12,681 --> 00:04:15,155
After senior year, who knows
how many of you will still be left.

50
00:04:15,179 --> 00:04:16,774
Oh, don't say that.

51
00:04:16,859 --> 00:04:18,583
These two are in it for the long haul.

52
00:04:18,602 --> 00:04:19,816
They've been friends since they were kids.

53
00:04:19,840 --> 00:04:21,580
So they'll keep going together, right?

54
00:04:22,253 --> 00:04:23,078
That's enough, Mom.

55
00:04:23,110 --> 00:04:25,530
I'm just telling the truth.
No harm in that.

56
00:04:25,580 --> 00:04:26,703
Right, Tanrak, dear?

57
00:04:27,859 --> 00:04:29,902
Well, I…

58
00:04:30,146 --> 00:04:31,146
Tell me.

59
00:04:31,522 --> 00:04:34,002
I've got soda.

60
00:04:34,262 --> 00:04:35,262
Anyone want some?

61
00:04:35,370 --> 00:04:36,327
Yeah, I do.

62
00:04:36,354 --> 00:04:38,174
But I don't have a cup.

63
00:04:38,204 --> 00:04:39,222
I'll go get it.

64
00:04:39,346 --> 00:04:42,601
Barth, you can just share mine.

65
00:04:45,134 --> 00:04:46,134
Okay.

66
00:04:53,210 --> 00:04:55,800
Tanrak, are you still keeping up
with your prayers?

67
00:04:56,576 --> 00:04:57,576
Yes, I am.

68
00:04:58,171 --> 00:05:00,395
Why didn't you come visit me during break?

69
00:05:00,425 --> 00:05:01,637
I was looking forward to that.

70
00:05:01,663 --> 00:05:03,302
The orchard was full of fruit.

71
00:05:14,950 --> 00:05:15,950
Tan.

72
00:05:16,031 --> 00:05:17,031
Hm?

73
00:05:18,503 --> 00:05:19,850
Do whatever you want, okay?

74
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:26,097
What my parents said…

75
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:28,520
you don't have to take it so seriously.

76
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:30,960
Oh.

77
00:05:32,134 --> 00:05:34,201
Yeah, it's fine.

78
00:05:37,924 --> 00:05:39,530
And where did your rosary go?

79
00:05:40,780 --> 00:05:41,980
I haven't seen you wearing it.

80
00:05:42,931 --> 00:05:44,500
Don't you usually keep it on you?

81
00:05:47,034 --> 00:05:48,096
Oh. Right.

82
00:05:49,613 --> 00:05:51,250
I don't know where I left it.

83
00:06:02,020 --> 00:06:03,251
I ran into Barth

84
00:06:03,934 --> 00:06:04,934
at the football field.

85
00:06:05,983 --> 00:06:07,173
He dropped it.

86
00:06:08,620 --> 00:06:11,902
But I don't know
if I should give it back to you

87
00:06:12,105 --> 00:06:13,398
or give it back to him.

88
00:06:59,192 --> 00:07:00,192
Come on.

89
00:07:00,851 --> 00:07:01,851
Oh, Tanrak.

90
00:07:02,287 --> 00:07:03,570
Why are you standing here alone?

91
00:07:03,842 --> 00:07:05,696
Oh, I was going to shower.

92
00:07:07,961 --> 00:07:10,400
Put these two in my room.

93
00:07:10,419 --> 00:07:12,500
And the other two in Father's room.

94
00:07:16,588 --> 00:07:18,299
Barth, go.

95
00:07:25,950 --> 00:07:27,195
Just put it on the table.

96
00:07:27,520 --> 00:07:28,520
Sure.

97
00:07:36,059 --> 00:07:37,059
Oops.

98
00:07:37,613 --> 00:07:38,613
Sorry.

99
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:51,450
APPLICATION FOR ADMISSION
TO A BACHELOR'S DEGREE PROGRAM

100
00:07:55,802 --> 00:07:57,201
Sorry, I didn't mean to.

101
00:07:57,680 --> 00:08:00,300
It's okay. I'll clean it up.

102
00:08:09,611 --> 00:08:11,210
You used to take football seriously?

103
00:08:11,230 --> 00:08:12,650
You even have cleats.

104
00:08:13,180 --> 00:08:15,303
I almost got into university
on a football quota.

105
00:08:18,419 --> 00:08:20,610
But I guess I was too good back then.

106
00:08:21,234 --> 00:08:24,450
Father was probably scared
I'd run off and become a footballer.

107
00:08:26,303 --> 00:08:27,543
So, yeah. That's what happened.

108
00:08:28,580 --> 00:08:29,696
Really?

109
00:08:30,940 --> 00:08:32,299
You were really serious about it.

110
00:08:33,727 --> 00:08:34,727
Yeah.

111
00:08:36,828 --> 00:08:37,828
You know what?

112
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:40,460
Back then,

113
00:08:41,874 --> 00:08:43,700
I used to pray to God

114
00:08:45,220 --> 00:08:46,696
to let me get that quota.

115
00:08:49,462 --> 00:08:50,502
I told Him,

116
00:08:51,790 --> 00:08:53,202
“If You let me get in,

117
00:08:54,340 --> 00:08:56,204
I'll pray a hundred rosaries for You.”

118
00:09:00,570 --> 00:09:02,385
I asked Him to lead me
to the football field.

119
00:09:04,737 --> 00:09:05,971
But He…

120
00:09:06,970 --> 00:09:08,650
put me on this path instead.

121
00:09:17,463 --> 00:09:18,705
Do you ever miss it?

122
00:09:30,502 --> 00:09:31,502
I do miss it.

123
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:36,090
But I don't regret it.

124
00:09:39,266 --> 00:09:41,440
Because I know
if I hadn't chosen to stay here,

125
00:09:43,088 --> 00:09:48,103
I'd regret that even more
for not listening to what I really wanted.

126
00:09:52,229 --> 00:09:54,102
So now, I'm thankful to Him instead

127
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:57,297
for making my own voice
loud enough for me to hear.

128
00:10:06,970 --> 00:10:08,400
Here. It's yours.

129
00:10:15,733 --> 00:10:16,733
What about you?

130
00:10:17,305 --> 00:10:18,850
What are you gonna do with your life?

131
00:10:20,315 --> 00:10:21,574
You already know.

132
00:10:22,788 --> 00:10:27,300
- Why ask?
- Barth, just behave yourself.

133
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,597
And finish school.

134
00:10:29,480 --> 00:10:31,171
You're already on probation, you know.

135
00:10:32,437 --> 00:10:33,437
I know.

136
00:10:34,389 --> 00:10:37,303
Father had no problem kicking Kongkit out.

137
00:10:37,945 --> 00:10:39,300
So don't get too cocky.

138
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:52,536
Who do you think from my class

139
00:10:53,134 --> 00:10:54,302
will continue?

140
00:10:54,960 --> 00:10:56,497
Fewer than five, for sure.

141
00:10:58,002 --> 00:10:59,602
Kongdech, definitely.

142
00:11:00,620 --> 00:11:02,197
Pong might make it.

143
00:11:03,285 --> 00:11:05,197
Ta. Thana.

144
00:11:06,410 --> 00:11:07,699
The rest…

145
00:11:09,441 --> 00:11:10,441
I don't know.

146
00:11:18,180 --> 00:11:19,499
What about Tanrak?

147
00:11:36,270 --> 00:11:37,530
Aren't you close to him?

148
00:11:40,032 --> 00:11:41,102
What do you think?

149
00:12:07,350 --> 00:12:08,350
What are you doing?

150
00:12:11,980 --> 00:12:13,400
Getting ready for tomorrow's Mass.

151
00:12:13,788 --> 00:12:14,788
Oh.

152
00:12:15,768 --> 00:12:16,768
Okay.

153
00:12:17,656 --> 00:12:20,896
So, where did you go for New Year?

154
00:12:23,340 --> 00:12:25,017
I took my sibling out on the motorbike

155
00:12:25,432 --> 00:12:26,432
to watch fireworks.

156
00:12:29,042 --> 00:12:30,042
Nice.

157
00:12:30,480 --> 00:12:32,201
I was…

158
00:12:32,860 --> 00:12:34,497
stuck at school all break.

159
00:12:35,251 --> 00:12:36,902
Nothing to do. So boring.

160
00:12:37,961 --> 00:12:39,930
And I had to be with Barth the whole time.

161
00:12:41,764 --> 00:12:42,764
Right.

162
00:12:46,177 --> 00:12:47,899
That's how your rosary ended up with him.

163
00:12:53,687 --> 00:12:55,397
Yeah, so…

164
00:12:55,614 --> 00:12:57,269
I came to thank you.

165
00:12:57,293 --> 00:12:58,994
I haven't said thanks yet.

166
00:12:59,783 --> 00:13:00,783
No problem.

167
00:13:01,300 --> 00:13:04,148
I was trying to figure out where I put it

168
00:13:05,035 --> 00:13:06,297
or if I lent it to someone.

169
00:13:07,730 --> 00:13:09,198
But nothing's going on, okay?

170
00:13:12,642 --> 00:13:14,382
I never said anything was going on.

171
00:13:19,917 --> 00:13:21,097
Or is something going on?

172
00:13:36,410 --> 00:13:37,453
Nothing's going on.

173
00:13:41,462 --> 00:13:43,103
See you in the movie room.

174
00:14:04,605 --> 00:14:07,170
2, 3…

175
00:14:08,534 --> 00:14:09,534
4, 5.

176
00:14:11,536 --> 00:14:12,604
What is it, Tanrak?

177
00:14:15,328 --> 00:14:16,328
Huh?

178
00:14:18,451 --> 00:14:20,383
The rosary I lent you.

179
00:14:20,602 --> 00:14:22,398
Kongdech returned it to me.

180
00:14:22,991 --> 00:14:24,200
I think

181
00:14:25,871 --> 00:14:27,496
he must be suspicious about us.

182
00:14:28,902 --> 00:14:30,402
Calm down. It's nothing.

183
00:14:31,550 --> 00:14:32,702
What if he tells Father?

184
00:14:35,893 --> 00:14:36,973
You think he'd tell Father?

185
00:14:39,539 --> 00:14:41,600
Barth, we're screwed.

186
00:14:46,430 --> 00:14:48,800
It's just a rosary.
People can borrow those, right?

187
00:14:49,830 --> 00:14:50,830
Right?

188
00:14:51,592 --> 00:14:52,592
It's nothing.

189
00:14:53,038 --> 00:14:54,038
Just let it go for now.

190
00:14:55,164 --> 00:14:56,164
Okay?

191
00:14:57,845 --> 00:14:58,995
Don't get too worked up.

192
00:14:59,847 --> 00:15:00,847
It's nothing.

193
00:15:02,044 --> 00:15:06,499
But I think lately,
we've been too obvious.

194
00:15:09,950 --> 00:15:11,598
I'm acting the same as always.

195
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:15,090
No one's gonna know.

196
00:15:16,220 --> 00:15:17,296
Don't stress.

197
00:15:19,570 --> 00:15:20,570
It's nothing.

198
00:15:21,152 --> 00:15:22,152
Yeah.

199
00:15:22,682 --> 00:15:24,610
We should still be careful.

200
00:15:26,580 --> 00:15:28,002
I don't want to draw attention.

201
00:15:30,450 --> 00:15:31,450
Okay?

202
00:15:31,792 --> 00:15:32,792
Okay.

203
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,300
Don't worry too much.

204
00:15:36,370 --> 00:15:37,370
Calm down.

205
00:15:37,730 --> 00:15:38,730
It's nothing.

206
00:15:39,260 --> 00:15:41,001
I said we should be careful.

207
00:15:41,220 --> 00:15:42,851
No one's here.

208
00:15:49,070 --> 00:15:50,897
I was the first one in Master Phak's room.

209
00:15:51,961 --> 00:15:52,961
You're bragging.

210
00:15:53,608 --> 00:15:54,699
I'm serious.

211
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:56,377
I even found cleats in there.

212
00:15:58,991 --> 00:16:01,903
So, if you were Master Phak,
what would you do?

213
00:16:04,244 --> 00:16:05,977
I think I'd keep playing football.

214
00:16:07,002 --> 00:16:08,810
No matter who says it's right or wrong.

215
00:16:10,911 --> 00:16:11,911
Really?

216
00:16:12,330 --> 00:16:13,502
But I think

217
00:16:13,688 --> 00:16:14,997
he's already made his choice.

218
00:16:15,810 --> 00:16:16,810
You think so?

219
00:16:17,019 --> 00:16:19,011
If it were you,
would you really give up your dream?

220
00:16:19,035 --> 00:16:20,200
Oh, Kongdech.

221
00:16:24,462 --> 00:16:25,462
You…

222
00:16:25,872 --> 00:16:26,872
can sit here.

223
00:16:30,656 --> 00:16:31,899
Help me…

224
00:16:32,499 --> 00:16:34,198
make some leaves.

225
00:16:36,346 --> 00:16:37,699
Okay. How do I do it?

226
00:16:39,309 --> 00:16:41,087
Fold it like this.

227
00:16:41,118 --> 00:16:43,499
So it comes out… like.

228
00:16:43,920 --> 00:16:45,302
(Wanna talk outside?)

229
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:49,730
(Later.)

230
00:16:52,974 --> 00:16:54,242
So it looks like this.

231
00:16:57,118 --> 00:16:58,118
(When?)

232
00:17:00,691 --> 00:17:01,691
Like this?

233
00:17:01,717 --> 00:17:02,896
Yeah, like that.

234
00:17:04,223 --> 00:17:07,402
Barth, can you cut this for me?

235
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:12,804
How do I cut it?

236
00:17:12,810 --> 00:17:14,810
MUSIC ROOM

237
00:17:16,810 --> 00:17:17,810
Cut it like this.

238
00:17:18,660 --> 00:17:19,800
Am I doing this right?

239
00:17:20,853 --> 00:17:21,853
Let me see.

240
00:17:22,358 --> 00:17:23,497
No, it's like this.

241
00:17:26,120 --> 00:17:28,296
No, you need to layer them.

242
00:17:29,720 --> 00:17:31,180
No, like this.

243
00:17:31,896 --> 00:17:33,582
It needs to twist around.

244
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:42,770
JUST TALK?

245
00:17:46,259 --> 00:17:47,259
Got it?

246
00:17:47,920 --> 00:17:48,920
All good, right?

247
00:17:49,110 --> 00:17:50,110
Yep.

248
00:17:50,807 --> 00:17:51,900
Do I cut this too?

249
00:17:52,182 --> 00:17:53,400
Yeah, cut it too.

250
00:18:03,020 --> 00:18:04,099
Looks good.

251
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:06,800
This one.

252
00:18:44,180 --> 00:18:47,503
♪ There is a truth I want you to know ♪

253
00:18:47,950 --> 00:18:51,202
♪ Meanings many words seem to hold ♪

254
00:18:51,590 --> 00:18:54,770
♪ No matter how beautiful they may be ♪

255
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:58,530
BARTH TANRAK

256
00:18:59,001 --> 00:19:02,271
♪ Everything I do for you ♪

257
00:19:02,706 --> 00:19:05,973
♪ May reflect what my heart holds true ♪

258
00:19:06,431 --> 00:19:09,400
♪ Maybe my eyes already show ♪

259
00:19:09,423 --> 00:19:12,400
♪ The feelings in my heart that flow ♪

260
00:19:12,840 --> 00:19:19,703
♪ But do you know it's so much more? ♪

261
00:19:20,145 --> 00:19:25,697
♪ Things I would like to give to you ♪

262
00:19:26,905 --> 00:19:28,783
♪ I'd gather every star ♪

263
00:19:28,805 --> 00:19:32,379
♪ To show all the love I have for you ♪

264
00:19:32,720 --> 00:19:34,499
♪ And make every song belong to you ♪

265
00:19:34,520 --> 00:19:36,330
WANNA HEAR YOU SING EVERY DAY

266
00:19:36,362 --> 00:19:41,797
♪ To tell you I love you
more than words could say ♪

267
00:19:41,942 --> 00:19:43,450
♪ Through seasons change ♪

268
00:19:43,750 --> 00:19:45,840
♪ I'll spend with you
my every single breath ♪

269
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:50,130
(WANNA HEAR YOU SING EVERY DAY)
(WHAT'S YOUR FAVORITE NOTE?) (YOU'RE MY FAVORITE NOTE)

270
00:19:50,167 --> 00:19:53,100
♪ No words can replace ♪

271
00:19:53,681 --> 00:19:59,597
♪ What my heart means
when it says I love you ♪

272
00:20:00,340 --> 00:20:04,502
♪ Let this love song speak for my heart ♪

273
00:20:04,783 --> 00:20:07,666
♪ Which belongs only to you ♪

274
00:20:08,442 --> 00:20:14,382
♪ Let it be the promise of our love
until the time is through ♪

275
00:20:20,371 --> 00:20:21,560
♪ I'd gather every star ♪

276
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:26,170
EVER SINCE I MET YOU,
LOVE SONGS SOUND MUCH SWEETER

277
00:20:26,251 --> 00:20:29,648
♪ And make every song belong to you ♪

278
00:20:29,682 --> 00:20:35,198
♪ To tell you I love you
more than words could say ♪

279
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:37,970
HOW WAS YOUR DAY?

280
00:20:38,004 --> 00:20:43,173
♪ I'll spend with you
my every single breath ♪

281
00:20:43,724 --> 00:20:46,551
♪ No words can replace ♪

282
00:20:47,198 --> 00:20:54,720
♪ What my heart means
when it says I love you ♪

283
00:20:54,760 --> 00:20:56,770
TAN KHAM WA RAK

284
00:22:23,097 --> 00:22:24,097
Hey, hurry up.

285
00:22:24,210 --> 00:22:26,801
Disc two's about to start.
If you're slow, I'm not waiting.

286
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:52,290
CAN WE MEET DURING MOVIE TIME? — TRAB

287
00:23:33,040 --> 00:23:35,650
N.A.T.
SECOND HALF OLD BUILDING.
STORAGE ROOM — NAT

288
00:23:37,951 --> 00:23:39,497
That name suits you.

289
00:23:47,546 --> 00:23:48,546
Hey.

290
00:24:06,517 --> 00:24:07,517
I'm tired.

291
00:24:11,770 --> 00:24:12,896
Me too.

292
00:24:13,231 --> 00:24:14,499
We walked all this way.

293
00:24:17,007 --> 00:24:18,201
I mean…

294
00:24:21,250 --> 00:24:23,097
I'm tired of hiding us.

295
00:24:33,911 --> 00:24:35,103
Is it worth it, then?

296
00:24:45,368 --> 00:24:46,368
Not yet.

297
00:24:52,832 --> 00:24:53,974
Still not worth it.

298
00:25:17,390 --> 00:25:18,390
Worth it now?

299
00:25:19,470 --> 00:25:20,470
Hm?

300
00:26:06,911 --> 00:26:07,911
Barth.

301
00:26:20,918 --> 00:26:21,918
Barth.

302
00:26:40,157 --> 00:26:41,157
Shit!

303
00:27:54,700 --> 00:27:55,700
He's gone.

304
00:28:00,190 --> 00:28:01,190
You go.

305
00:28:06,256 --> 00:28:07,400
Are you okay?

306
00:28:07,470 --> 00:28:08,470
Just go.

307
00:28:41,281 --> 00:28:42,281
Tanrak.

308
00:28:53,564 --> 00:28:54,797
Is the movie over?

309
00:28:59,056 --> 00:29:00,056
Not yet.

310
00:29:02,240 --> 00:29:05,402
I just remembered I forgot something.

311
00:29:10,590 --> 00:29:11,900
Is everything okay?

312
00:29:15,580 --> 00:29:16,580
Everything's fine.

313
00:29:20,330 --> 00:29:22,454
About Brother Joe's activity next week,

314
00:29:23,317 --> 00:29:25,174
let me know if you need anything.

315
00:29:29,020 --> 00:29:30,020
Yes, Father.

316
00:30:28,417 --> 00:30:29,970
<i>But the question is,</i>

317
00:30:30,691 --> 00:30:34,450
does every kind of love
lead us closer to Him?

318
00:30:35,422 --> 00:30:37,499
<i>Some love makes us sacrifice.</i>

319
00:30:37,884 --> 00:30:41,195
<i>Some love makes us
want to become better people.</i>

320
00:30:42,130 --> 00:30:45,450
<i>But some love makes us hide.</i>

321
00:30:46,200 --> 00:30:47,597
<i>It makes us afraid.</i>

322
00:30:48,019 --> 00:30:49,397
<i>It makes us feel guilty.</i>

323
00:30:49,670 --> 00:30:51,148
But are you happy?

324
00:30:57,511 --> 00:31:01,004
<i>If some feelings make you feel bad,</i>

325
00:31:01,360 --> 00:31:02,960
is that wrong, Father?

326
00:31:03,444 --> 00:31:05,000
Sometimes it isn't wrong.

327
00:31:05,810 --> 00:31:07,398
<i>But it makes you afraid.</i>

328
00:31:08,170 --> 00:31:09,697
<i>Afraid you'll do wrong.</i>

329
00:31:12,808 --> 00:31:15,397
I want to be in heaven with my parents.

330
00:31:15,549 --> 00:31:17,201
Your life is good, isn't it?

331
00:31:18,450 --> 00:31:20,050
If one day I have to choose,

332
00:31:22,025 --> 00:31:24,690
I'd choose God over anything else.

333
00:31:46,400 --> 00:31:49,697
<i>When we feel we must hide from God's gaze,</i>

334
00:31:50,388 --> 00:31:53,099
<i>it may not be because He doesn't love us.</i>

335
00:31:54,194 --> 00:31:57,582
<i>It may be because our hearts are confused.</i>

336
00:32:21,750 --> 00:32:22,750
Hello.

337
00:33:54,180 --> 00:33:55,186
Hello, boys.

338
00:33:55,863 --> 00:33:57,296
- Hello.
- Hi.

339
00:33:57,343 --> 00:33:58,343
Are you tired?

340
00:33:58,370 --> 00:33:59,197
Not really.

341
00:33:59,232 --> 00:34:00,232
Not really?

342
00:34:01,096 --> 00:34:02,198
Okay.

343
00:34:02,980 --> 00:34:05,699
Welcome to the Shine of Grace Foundation.

344
00:34:06,425 --> 00:34:07,700
Come on in with me.

345
00:34:11,837 --> 00:34:14,550
Here, we're committed to taking in
young people who lack opportunities

346
00:34:14,574 --> 00:34:15,980
and have no one to turn to.

347
00:34:16,134 --> 00:34:17,977
We welcome them into God's embrace

348
00:34:18,743 --> 00:34:20,600
to help heal the wounds of their past

349
00:34:21,001 --> 00:34:24,099
and turn loneliness
into a sense of self-worth.

350
00:34:25,762 --> 00:34:30,702
Okay, now I'll have each of the seniors
introduce themselves.

351
00:34:30,720 --> 00:34:33,250
Everyone will do a signature pose too.

352
00:34:33,830 --> 00:34:35,197
Let's start with the first one.

353
00:34:36,140 --> 00:34:38,602
My name is Tanrak.

354
00:34:40,554 --> 00:34:41,703
This is Tanrak.

355
00:34:42,309 --> 00:34:43,309
Next.

356
00:34:43,910 --> 00:34:45,998
My name is Kongdech.

357
00:34:49,795 --> 00:34:52,130
Let's count
how many beads are on a rosary.

358
00:34:52,709 --> 00:34:53,709
See?

359
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:57,438
Mine has 53 beads in total.

360
00:35:11,155 --> 00:35:12,602
Will you come again?

361
00:35:14,414 --> 00:35:15,580
Of course I will.

362
00:35:15,967 --> 00:35:17,198
Why do you ask? Hm?

363
00:35:18,555 --> 00:35:20,497
You're kind, just like Brother Joe.

364
00:35:20,940 --> 00:35:22,500
Wow.

365
00:35:22,872 --> 00:35:25,179
Just tell me what you want to eat.

366
00:35:26,380 --> 00:35:28,397
You're going to be a priest, right?

367
00:35:34,785 --> 00:35:35,986
Whether I become one or not,

368
00:35:36,430 --> 00:35:38,198
I'll still come see you.

369
00:35:38,893 --> 00:35:39,893
Here.

370
00:35:43,920 --> 00:35:44,782
I promise.

371
00:35:44,819 --> 00:35:45,819
Okay.

372
00:35:48,134 --> 00:35:50,202
All right, now that we're done singing,

373
00:35:50,348 --> 00:35:51,579
let's have some snacks.

374
00:35:51,717 --> 00:35:52,899
Who wants snacks?

375
00:35:53,616 --> 00:35:54,616
Let's go.

376
00:36:00,990 --> 00:36:01,990
Tanrak.

377
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:04,597
Who wants one? Raise your hand.

378
00:36:06,629 --> 00:36:07,629
How many pieces?

379
00:36:11,080 --> 00:36:12,450
Did everyone get snacks?

380
00:36:12,862 --> 00:36:13,355
Okay.

381
00:36:13,380 --> 00:36:15,198
Whoever jumps the highest gets a snack.

382
00:36:15,376 --> 00:36:17,985
Hey! Nice. Here, take one.

383
00:36:18,071 --> 00:36:19,071
High five.

384
00:36:19,374 --> 00:36:21,410
Mm. Go on, eat it.

385
00:36:21,785 --> 00:36:22,785
Here.

386
00:36:24,195 --> 00:36:28,002
<i>Well, I've always pictured myself that way.</i>

387
00:36:28,497 --> 00:36:29,696
<i>A priest's robe.</i>

388
00:36:30,114 --> 00:36:31,000
<i>The altar.</i>

389
00:36:31,137 --> 00:36:33,102
<i>And me standing there preaching.</i>

390
00:36:33,745 --> 00:36:35,604
<i>That's the picture I see most often.</i>

391
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:42,200
<i>if one day I have to choose,
I'd choose God over anything else.</i>

392
00:36:50,510 --> 00:36:52,401
Wow, can you do it?

393
00:38:32,859 --> 00:38:33,900
<i>Hello.</i>

394
00:38:34,456 --> 00:38:36,099
<i>This is Busaya.</i>

395
00:38:36,568 --> 00:38:39,299
<i>Please leave a message.</i>

396
00:38:41,761 --> 00:38:43,699
How do I do this again? I forgot.

397
00:38:44,014 --> 00:38:45,568
Mom, I've shown you so many times.

398
00:38:45,592 --> 00:38:46,914
Here, I'll record it for you.

399
00:38:46,937 --> 00:38:48,370
So you can watch it again.

400
00:38:48,459 --> 00:38:50,096
I just can't remember.

401
00:38:50,434 --> 00:38:51,237
What do I do?

402
00:38:51,262 --> 00:38:52,534
Pick up the phone first.

403
00:38:52,560 --> 00:38:53,296
Like this?

404
00:38:53,322 --> 00:38:54,100
Yes.

405
00:38:54,228 --> 00:38:56,699
Then press the orange button.

406
00:38:57,004 --> 00:38:57,642
This one?

407
00:38:57,668 --> 00:38:58,668
Yes.

408
00:39:00,764 --> 00:39:01,764
Now say it.

409
00:39:02,699 --> 00:39:03,997
Uh, hello.

410
00:39:04,540 --> 00:39:05,810
This is Busaya.

411
00:39:06,933 --> 00:39:09,000
Please leave a message.

412
00:39:11,268 --> 00:39:12,014
That's it.

413
00:39:12,041 --> 00:39:12,897
Now what?

414
00:39:12,922 --> 00:39:14,367
Now you can hang up.

415
00:39:14,394 --> 00:39:15,063
Hang up.

416
00:39:15,085 --> 00:39:16,195
Do I press this too?

417
00:39:16,225 --> 00:39:17,404
Yes, press it.

418
00:39:19,591 --> 00:39:20,349
That's it?

419
00:39:20,373 --> 00:39:21,570
That's it, Mom.

420
00:39:22,933 --> 00:39:23,837
Stop recording.

421
00:39:23,865 --> 00:39:25,398
You looked so funny, Mom.

422
00:40:03,404 --> 00:40:04,404
Ready?

423
00:40:04,780 --> 00:40:06,299
Come on, let's take a group photo.

424
00:40:17,440 --> 00:40:19,530
A RESPONSIBLE STUDENT DISCIPLINED,
EAGER TO LEARN,

425
00:40:19,530 --> 00:40:21,536
AND DETERMINED A GOOD CHRISTIAN
SHOULD CONTINUE TO MAINTAIN…

426
00:40:21,560 --> 00:40:23,410
SCHOLARSHIP STUDENT REPORT BOOK

427
00:40:34,373 --> 00:40:35,897
Joe asked me to give this to you.

428
00:40:37,722 --> 00:40:38,896
It's a little crumpled.

429
00:40:39,389 --> 00:40:40,389
Sorry.

430
00:40:40,604 --> 00:40:42,398
It's okay. Thanks.

431
00:40:47,840 --> 00:40:50,960
(TANRAK SAWATDIRAKKUL)
HAS SERVED AS A YOUTH VOLUNTEER MAY GOD BLESS YOU ALWAYS

432
00:40:52,480 --> 00:40:53,976
Can I get your homework book?

433
00:40:54,825 --> 00:40:56,730
Father Arnon will write in it
tomorrow morning.

434
00:40:59,280 --> 00:41:00,899
Oh, sure.

435
00:41:25,257 --> 00:41:26,450
<i>Can I get your homework book?</i>

436
00:41:27,152 --> 00:41:29,002
<i>Father Arnon will write in it
tomorrow morning.</i>

437
00:43:24,760 --> 00:43:26,810
HOW WAS YOUR DAY? / WHAT'S UP?

438
00:43:50,640 --> 00:43:57,490
(WANNA HEAR YOU SING EVERY DAY)
(WHAT'S YOUR FAVORITE NOTE?) (YOU'RE MY FAVORITE NOTE)

439
00:45:27,693 --> 00:45:29,000
I was just…

440
00:45:31,640 --> 00:45:32,640
I…

441
00:45:35,890 --> 00:45:38,598
You saw the report book I wrote in,
didn't you?

442
00:45:43,328 --> 00:45:45,200
Yes, Father.

443
00:45:47,340 --> 00:45:48,601
Think carefully.

444
00:45:49,762 --> 00:45:51,002
Reflect on it.

445
00:46:00,700 --> 00:46:01,897
I know

446
00:46:02,510 --> 00:46:05,004
there was something in there
that shouldn't have been there.

447
00:46:06,140 --> 00:46:08,302
So you got rid of it, didn't you?

448
00:46:12,777 --> 00:46:14,802
There's nothing, Father.

449
00:46:24,060 --> 00:46:25,602
I believe one day

450
00:46:26,512 --> 00:46:28,771
you'll come and tell me yourself.

451
00:48:10,940 --> 00:48:11,940
So?

452
00:48:12,810 --> 00:48:14,800
Did Father catch what you were burning?

453
00:48:19,600 --> 00:48:20,802
What are you talking about?

454
00:48:22,440 --> 00:48:23,974
Your notes with Barth.

455
00:48:24,534 --> 00:48:25,534
Well?

456
00:48:25,958 --> 00:48:27,032
Did you burn them in time?

457
00:48:30,155 --> 00:48:31,897
Did you tell Father?

458
00:48:36,520 --> 00:48:37,520
No.

459
00:48:38,954 --> 00:48:40,096
I didn't tell him.

460
00:48:42,010 --> 00:48:43,302
You don't have to be scared.

461
00:48:44,355 --> 00:48:46,530
I don't like sticking my nose
into people's business.

462
00:48:48,980 --> 00:48:50,404
And I wish I'd never found out.

463
00:48:57,550 --> 00:49:00,102
I don't even know
what I'm more mad about, Tanrak.

464
00:49:03,786 --> 00:49:05,299
You and Barth

465
00:49:06,090 --> 00:49:07,300
hiding it from me,

466
00:49:09,680 --> 00:49:10,998
treating me like I'm stupid.

467
00:49:12,350 --> 00:49:14,004
Did you really think I wouldn't notice?

468
00:49:17,217 --> 00:49:19,899
Or the fact that you're not going
to seminary with me anymore.

469
00:49:21,373 --> 00:49:21,964
Kongdech!

470
00:49:21,988 --> 00:49:23,697
Either way, you betrayed me.

471
00:49:32,551 --> 00:49:34,100
I'm asking you seriously, Tanrak.

472
00:49:37,325 --> 00:49:39,102
That calling from God you hear,

473
00:49:40,820 --> 00:49:42,300
is it still as loud as it used to be?

474
00:49:47,110 --> 00:49:49,602
Don't you want to see your parents
in heaven anymore?

475
00:49:57,540 --> 00:49:59,405
I believed we'd get ordained together.

476
00:52:13,188 --> 00:52:14,188
Tanrak.

477
00:52:17,450 --> 00:52:19,176
How long are you gonna keep avoiding me?

478
00:52:20,910 --> 00:52:23,303
What's your excuse
for not talking to me this time?

479
00:52:26,183 --> 00:52:27,586
I have nothing to say.

480
00:52:30,450 --> 00:52:32,299
Tanrak, what's wrong with you?

481
00:52:34,680 --> 00:52:37,320
You keep shutting me out like this.
I don't even know what's wrong.

482
00:52:37,386 --> 00:52:38,946
Just tell me what the hell I did wrong.

483
00:52:39,385 --> 00:52:40,400
Keep your voice down.

484
00:52:42,605 --> 00:52:44,377
Tan, just tell me. Talk to me.

485
00:52:44,425 --> 00:52:46,102
I don't even know what I did wrong.

486
00:52:46,150 --> 00:52:47,497
I said keep it down.

487
00:52:48,700 --> 00:52:49,940
Then what do you want me to do?

488
00:52:50,044 --> 00:52:51,297
Kongdech knows.

489
00:52:59,310 --> 00:53:00,395
Who else knows?

490
00:53:01,850 --> 00:53:03,398
Who else knows? Does Father know?

491
00:53:04,600 --> 00:53:06,099
Who else knows, Tan?

492
00:53:09,466 --> 00:53:11,001
Tan, who else knows?

493
00:53:11,602 --> 00:53:13,122
Does Father know? Do our friends know?

494
00:53:14,608 --> 00:53:15,534
Tanrak, who else knows?

495
00:53:15,551 --> 00:53:16,780
I don't know!

496
00:53:18,300 --> 00:53:19,602
I don't know either.

497
00:53:23,611 --> 00:53:24,611
Barth.

498
00:53:27,291 --> 00:53:28,300
I'm tired.

499
00:53:30,220 --> 00:53:31,395
And I'm scared.

500
00:53:35,792 --> 00:53:37,176
And I'm not happy at all.

501
00:53:40,484 --> 00:53:41,484
Tanrak.

502
00:53:42,897 --> 00:53:44,699
I can make you happy.

503
00:53:45,237 --> 00:53:46,797
Just let go of everything for a second.

504
00:53:48,016 --> 00:53:49,475
Tan, wait. Calm down.

505
00:53:49,503 --> 00:53:50,503
Talk to me first.

506
00:53:50,645 --> 00:53:52,000
Tan, talk to me first.

507
00:53:54,074 --> 00:53:55,074
Tan.

508
00:53:55,491 --> 00:53:56,491
Barth!

509
00:54:01,640 --> 00:54:03,000
Don't follow me.

510
00:54:03,757 --> 00:54:05,103
I'm begging you, Barth.

511
00:54:06,042 --> 00:54:07,170
Where are you going now?

512
00:54:07,890 --> 00:54:10,405
You haven't talked to me all week.
Where else are you gonna go?

513
00:54:21,440 --> 00:54:23,700
Seriously, what the hell has God
ever done for you?

514
00:54:23,976 --> 00:54:25,499
All that praying you're about to do.

515
00:54:26,370 --> 00:54:27,800
Talk to me instead.

516
00:54:28,540 --> 00:54:30,102
Why the hell do you keep praying?

517
00:54:30,522 --> 00:54:32,100
Has it ever f*cking helped you?

518
00:54:36,110 --> 00:54:37,397
What did you just say?

519
00:54:38,380 --> 00:54:39,380
Huh?

520
00:54:40,520 --> 00:54:41,520
I'm sorry.

521
00:54:45,000 --> 00:54:46,696
Tan, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

522
00:54:48,080 --> 00:54:49,096
I didn't mean it.

523
00:54:52,331 --> 00:54:53,900
I just wanted to talk to you.

524
00:54:57,210 --> 00:54:59,099
I didn't mean it. I didn't. I'm sorry.

525
00:54:59,890 --> 00:55:00,890
Tan.

526
00:55:03,678 --> 00:55:05,600
I really didn't mean it.
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

527
00:55:09,488 --> 00:55:10,488
Tanrak!

528
00:56:57,740 --> 00:56:58,740
Father.

529
00:57:03,720 --> 00:57:05,297
Can you please talk to me?

530
00:57:18,183 --> 00:57:19,183
Father.

531
00:57:21,262 --> 00:57:22,600
I'm in love

532
00:57:25,111 --> 00:57:26,700
even though I know it's wrong.

533
00:57:29,322 --> 00:57:31,174
I tried to stop myself.

534
00:57:33,020 --> 00:57:34,397
But I couldn't.

535
00:57:36,779 --> 00:57:38,100
I'm angry at myself

536
00:57:39,862 --> 00:57:41,804
for not being able to control it.

537
00:57:49,952 --> 00:57:50,952
Father.

538
00:57:52,934 --> 00:57:53,982
I'm scared.

539
00:57:57,360 --> 00:57:59,497
I'm scared God will reject me.

540
00:58:02,717 --> 00:58:05,198
God would never reject you, Tanrak.

541
00:58:06,100 --> 00:58:08,894
He always loves you.

542
00:58:12,632 --> 00:58:14,376
Love isn't wrong.

543
00:58:16,120 --> 00:58:20,896
God created humans
with hearts and feelings.

544
00:58:22,056 --> 00:58:23,801
But our actions

545
00:58:24,680 --> 00:58:26,699
are what we must take responsibility for.

546
00:58:29,240 --> 00:58:31,699
I want you to think carefully

547
00:58:34,090 --> 00:58:38,004
about where this love is leading you.

548
00:58:40,244 --> 00:58:42,600
But the fact that you're here now

549
00:58:43,595 --> 00:58:48,100
means you still want to be with Him.

550
00:58:53,090 --> 00:58:55,500
If you believe that it's wrong,

551
00:58:56,874 --> 00:58:58,720
then you need to figure out

552
00:58:59,410 --> 00:59:02,696
how to make amends for this sin.

553
00:59:26,022 --> 00:59:27,198
If…

554
00:59:29,250 --> 00:59:30,699
If I break up with him,

555
00:59:34,448 --> 00:59:36,099
you'll forgive me, right?

556
00:59:43,250 --> 00:59:46,503
God always forgives those
who repent, Tanrak.

557
00:59:49,180 --> 00:59:51,000
You need to ask yourself

558
00:59:53,590 --> 00:59:56,102
whether you want to stay with that love

559
00:59:58,590 --> 01:00:00,299
or stay with Him.

560
01:00:04,931 --> 01:00:07,502
God always gives us a chance, Tanrak.

561
01:00:09,579 --> 01:00:11,299
But His path

562
01:00:12,934 --> 01:00:14,376
is not an easy one.

563
01:01:04,786 --> 01:01:05,786
Tanrak.

564
01:01:07,143 --> 01:01:08,200
Can we talk?

565
01:01:13,170 --> 01:01:14,371
Don't do this, Barth.

566
01:01:21,053 --> 01:01:23,800
You know this can't happen.

567
01:01:28,520 --> 01:01:29,980
There has to be a way.

568
01:01:31,400 --> 01:01:34,004
I still want to be with you.
I still want a future with you.

569
01:01:35,751 --> 01:01:37,751
Who cares if anyone says this is wrong?

570
01:01:37,774 --> 01:01:40,097
Even if God says it's wrong, I don't care.

571
01:01:40,361 --> 01:01:41,361
Barth.

572
01:01:42,528 --> 01:01:43,795
You can't just not care.

573
01:01:44,964 --> 01:01:45,997
We're students.

574
01:01:46,340 --> 01:01:47,398
We go to school here.

575
01:01:48,530 --> 01:01:49,902
We're scholarship students.

576
01:01:50,712 --> 01:01:51,997
You know that.

577
01:01:59,050 --> 01:02:00,050
I don't know.

578
01:02:01,900 --> 01:02:03,548
I don't know anything about God.

579
01:02:06,200 --> 01:02:07,468
I only know myself.

580
01:02:09,540 --> 01:02:11,973
I know I love you.

581
01:02:22,980 --> 01:02:23,980
Tanrak.

582
01:02:26,925 --> 01:02:27,925
What about you?

583
01:02:30,300 --> 01:02:32,379
Didn't you ever love me at all?

584
01:02:36,780 --> 01:02:38,002
I do love you.

585
01:02:39,400 --> 01:02:40,896
I love you so much.

586
01:02:46,937 --> 01:02:48,503
But what do we do with that?

587
01:02:58,299 --> 01:03:00,400
If God teaches us to love,

588
01:03:02,770 --> 01:03:04,595
but we're not allowed to love each other,

589
01:03:06,346 --> 01:03:08,397
then what's the point of having God
in this world?

590
01:03:45,030 --> 01:03:46,730
If this place isn't for us,

591
01:03:51,674 --> 01:03:53,002
let's run away together.

592
01:04:38,600 --> 01:04:40,890
(Next Episode)
God probably won't forgive me anytime soon.

593
01:04:41,211 --> 01:04:42,411
Let's forget about it for now.

594
01:04:42,645 --> 01:04:44,405
As long as I have you with me,
that's enough.

595
01:04:45,600 --> 01:04:49,183
Mom, Dad, are you still waiting
for me in heaven?

596
01:04:49,300 --> 01:04:50,601
Let me take care of Tanrak.

597
01:04:50,830 --> 01:04:52,198
Whoa!

598
01:04:54,001 --> 01:04:55,902
So what are you gonna do now?

599
01:04:56,330 --> 01:04:57,582
I don't know.

600
01:04:57,994 --> 01:05:00,520
I've spent most of my life
at Magdalene House.

601
01:05:00,733 --> 01:05:02,250
There's food and rent to worry about.

602
01:05:02,450 --> 01:05:03,850
It's hard, huh?

603
01:05:04,014 --> 01:05:05,014
That's just life.

604
01:05:07,000 --> 01:05:10,702
Do you think there's a place up there
for the two of us?
